President Donald J. Trump has announced the members of an official delegation from the United States to China to discuss the trade relationship between the two countries. The delegation includes Ambassador Terry Branstad, Secretary of the Treasury Steven Mnuchin, Secretary of Commerce Wilbur Ross, United States Trade Representative Robert Lighthizer, Assistant to the President for Economic Policy Larry Kudlow, Assistant to the President for Trade and Manufacturing Policy Peter Navarro, and Deputy Assistant to the President for International Economic Affairs Everett Eissenstat. The discussions will take place from May 3, 2018.